Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/node.c
+++ b/ext/dom/node.c
@@ -824,8 +824,10 @@ static bool dom_set_document_ref_obj_single(xmlNodePtr node, xmlDocPtr doc, php
 {
 	dom_object *childobj = php_dom_object_get_data(node);
 	if (childobj && !childobj->document) {
 		childobj->document = document;
-		document->refcount++;
+		if (document) {
+			document->refcount++;
+		}
 		return true;
 	}
 	return false;
 }'}`
responded: Perfect! I can see that in the `dom_set_document_ref_obj_single` function, `document` is used in two places:
1. Line 828: `childobj->document = document;` (this is safe even if document is NULL)
2. Line 829: `document->refcount++;` (this will crash if document is NULL)

The fix is to add a null check for `document` before dereferencing it. Let me create the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/node.c b/ext/dom/node.c
index 242e56ad2d3..0e954ad5947 100644
--- a/ext/dom/node.c
+++ b/ext/dom/node.c
@@ -826,7 +826,9 @@ static bool dom_set_document_ref_obj_single(xmlNodePtr node, xmlDocPtr doc, php_
 	dom_object *childobj = php_dom_object_get_data(node);
 	if (childobj && !childobj->document) {
 		childobj->document = document;
-		document->refcount++;
+		if (document) {
+			document->refcount++;
+		}
 		return true;
 	}
 	return false;

