1. Calls `xmlSetTreeDoc` to set the XML document pointer
2. Calls `dom_set_document_ref_obj_single` to handle PHP document reference counting

If `intern->document` is NULL, we should still call `xmlSetTreeDoc` but skip the PHP reference counting. The best fix is to modify the call site to only call `dom_set_document_pointers` when `intern->document` is not NULL, and handle the `xmlSetTreeDoc` call separately.

